p: For VP + F, the lowest and highest Enterobacteriaceae counts were from 2.55 ± 1.99 log cfu/g on day 16 to 3.75 ± 0.64 log cfu/g on day 0. For VP + S, the lowest and highest counts were from 0.67 ± 1.03 log cfu/g on day eigh to 3.75 ± 0.64 log cfu/g on day 0. Statistically significant differences ( p < 0.05) were found between all tested groups without VP + F, VP + S, APCS, and VPC.
